function(num) { // First round to two decimal places if needed var roundedToTwoDecimals = Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Check if the result after two-decimal rounding has a decimal part of .00 or .50+ var integerPart = Math.floor(roundedToTwoDecimals); var decimalPart = roundedToTwoDecimals - integerPart; if (decimalPart === 0) { return integerPart; // No decimal part, keep as integer } else if (decimalPart >= 0.5) { return Math.round(roundedToTwoDecimals); // Round to the nearest integer } else { return roundedToTwoDecimals; // Otherwise, keep the two-decimal format } }

function(num) { // First round to two decimal places if needed var roundedToTwoDecimals = Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Check if the result after two-decimal rounding has a decimal part of .00 or .50+ var integerPart = Math.floor(roundedToTwoDecimals); var decimalPart = roundedToTwoDecimals - integerPart; if (decimalPart === 0) { return integerPart; // No decimal part, keep as integer } else if (decimalPart >= 0.5) { return Math.round(roundedToTwoDecimals); // Round to the nearest integer } else { return roundedToTwoDecimals; // Otherwise, keep the two-decimal format } }

* def roundAwayFromZero =

function(num) { // First round to two decimal places if needed var roundedToTwoDecimals = Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Check if the result after two-decimal rounding has a decimal part of .00 or .50+ var integerPart = Math.floor(roundedToTwoDecimals); var decimalPart = roundedToTwoDecimals - integerPart; if (decimalPart === 0) { return integerPart; // No decimal part, keep as integer } else if (decimalPart >= 0.5) { return Math.round(roundedToTwoDecimals); // Round to the nearest integer } else { return roundedToTwoDecimals; // Otherwise, keep the two-decimal format } }

* def roundAwayFromZero =
1
function(num) { // First round to two decimal places if needed var roundedToTwoDecimals = Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Check if the result after two-decimal rounding has a decimal part of .00 or .50+ var integerPart = Math.floor(roundedToTwoDecimals); var decimalPart = roundedToTwoDecimals - integerPart; if (decimalPart === 0) { return integerPart; // No decimal part, keep as integer } else if (decimalPart >= 0.5) { return Math.round(roundedToTwoDecimals); // Round to the nearest integer } else { return roundedToTwoDecimals; // Otherwise, keep the two-decimal format } }

* def roundAwayFromZero =

function(num) { // First round to two decimal places if needed var roundedToTwoDecimals = Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Check if the result after two-decimal rounding has a decimal part of .00 or .50+ var integerPart = Math.floor(roundedToTwoDecimals); var decimalPart = roundedToTwoDecimals - integerPart; if (decimalPart === 0) { return integerPart; // No decimal part, keep as integer } else if (decimalPart >= 0.5) { return Math.round(roundedToTwoDecimals); // Round to the nearest integer } else { return roundedToTwoDecimals; // Otherwise, keep the two-decimal format } }

* def roundAwayFromZero =

function(num) { // First round to two decimal places if needed var roundedToTwoDecimals = Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Check if the result after two-decimal rounding has a decimal part of .00 or .50+ var integerPart = Math.floor(roundedToTwoDecimals); var decimalPart = roundedToTwoDecimals - integerPart; if (decimalPart === 0) { return integerPart; // No decimal part, keep as integer } else if (decimalPart >= 0.5) { return Math.round(roundedToTwoDecimals); // Round to the nearest integer } else { return roundedToTwoDecimals; // Otherwise, keep the two-decimal format } }

function(num) { // First round to two decimal places if needed var roundedToTwoDecimals = Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Check if the result after two-decimal rounding has a decimal part of .00 or .50+ var integerPart = Math.floor(roundedToTwoDecimals); var decimalPart = roundedToTwoDecimals - integerPart; if (decimalPart === 0) { return integerPart; // No decimal part, keep as integer } else if (decimalPart >= 0.5) { return Math.round(roundedToTwoDecimals); // Round to the nearest integer } else { return roundedToTwoDecimals; // Otherwise, keep the two-decimal format } }

function(num) { // First round to two decimal places if needed var roundedToTwoDecimals = Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Check if the result after two-decimal rounding has a decimal part of .00 or .50+ var integerPart = Math.floor(roundedToTwoDecimals); var decimalPart = roundedToTwoDecimals - integerPart; if (decimalPart === 0) { return integerPart; // No decimal part, keep as integer } else if (decimalPart >= 0.5) { return Math.round(roundedToTwoDecimals); // Round to the nearest integer } else { return roundedToTwoDecimals; // Otherwise, keep the two-decimal format } }

function(num) { // First round to two decimal places if needed var roundedToTwoDecimals = Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Check if the result after two-decimal rounding has a decimal part of .00 or .50+ var integerPart = Math.floor(roundedToTwoDecimals); var decimalPart = roundedToTwoDecimals - integerPart; if (decimalPart === 0) { return integerPart; // No decimal part, keep as integer } else if (decimalPart >= 0.5) { return Math.round(roundedToTwoDecimals); // Round to the nearest integer } else { return roundedToTwoDecimals; // Otherwise, keep the two-decimal format } }

function(num) { // First round to two decimal places if needed var roundedToTwoDecimals = Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Check if the result after two-decimal rounding has a decimal part of .00 or .50+ var integerPart = Math.floor(roundedToTwoDecimals); var decimalPart = roundedToTwoDecimals - integerPart; if (decimalPart === 0) { return integerPart; // No decimal part, keep as integer } else if (decimalPart >= 0.5) { return Math.round(roundedToTwoDecimals); // Round to the nearest integer } else { return roundedToTwoDecimals; // Otherwise, keep the two-decimal format } }

function(num) { // First round to two decimal places if needed var roundedToTwoDecimals = Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Check if the result after two-decimal rounding has a decimal part of .00 or .50+ var integerPart = Math.floor(roundedToTwoDecimals); var decimalPart = roundedToTwoDecimals - integerPart; if (decimalPart === 0) { return integerPart; // No decimal part, keep as integer } else if (decimalPart >= 0.5) { return Math.round(roundedToTwoDecimals); // Round to the nearest integer } else { return roundedToTwoDecimals; // Otherwise, keep the two-decimal format } }

function(num) { // First round to two decimal places if needed var roundedToTwoDecimals = Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Check if the result after two-decimal rounding has a decimal part of .00 or .50+ var integerPart = Math.floor(roundedToTwoDecimals); var decimalPart = roundedToTwoDecimals - integerPart; if (decimalPart === 0) { return integerPart; // No decimal part, keep as integer } else if (decimalPart >= 0.5) { return Math.round(roundedToTwoDecimals); // Round to the nearest integer } else { return roundedToTwoDecimals; // Otherwise, keep the two-decimal format } }

function(num) { // First round to two decimal places if needed var roundedToTwoDecimals = Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Check if the result after two-decimal rounding has a decimal part of .00 or .50+ var integerPart = Math.floor(roundedToTwoDecimals); var decimalPart = roundedToTwoDecimals - integerPart; if (decimalPart === 0) { return integerPart; // No decimal part, keep as integer } else if (decimalPart >= 0.5) { return Math.round(roundedToTwoDecimals); // Round to the nearest integer } else { return roundedToTwoDecimals; // Otherwise, keep the two-decimal format } }

function(num) { // First round to two decimal places if needed var roundedToTwoDecimals = Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Check if the result after two-decimal rounding has a decimal part of .00 or .50+ var integerPart = Math.floor(roundedToTwoDecimals); var decimalPart = roundedToTwoDecimals - integerPart; if (decimalPart === 0) { return integerPart; // No decimal part, keep as integer } else if (decimalPart >= 0.5) { return Math.round(roundedToTwoDecimals); // Round to the nearest integer } else { return roundedToTwoDecimals; // Otherwise, keep the two-decimal format } }

function(num) { // First round to two decimal places if needed var roundedToTwoDecimals = Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Check if the result after two-decimal rounding has a decimal part of .00 or .50+ var integerPart = Math.floor(roundedToTwoDecimals); var decimalPart = roundedToTwoDecimals - integerPart; if (decimalPart === 0) { return integerPart; // No decimal part, keep as integer } else if (decimalPart >= 0.5) { return Math.round(roundedToTwoDecimals); // Round to the nearest integer } else { return roundedToTwoDecimals; // Otherwise, keep the two-decimal format } }

function(num) { // First round to two decimal places if needed var roundedToTwoDecimals = Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Check if the result after two-decimal rounding has a decimal part of .00 or .50+ var integerPart = Math.floor(roundedToTwoDecimals); var decimalPart = roundedToTwoDecimals - integerPart; if (decimalPart === 0) { return integerPart; // No decimal part, keep as integer } else if (decimalPart >= 0.5) { return Math.round(roundedToTwoDecimals); // Round to the nearest integer } else { return roundedToTwoDecimals; // Otherwise, keep the two-decimal format } }

function(num) { // First round to two decimal places if needed var roundedToTwoDecimals = Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Check if the result after two-decimal rounding has a decimal part of .00 or .50+ var integerPart = Math.floor(roundedToTwoDecimals); var decimalPart = roundedToTwoDecimals - integerPart; if (decimalPart === 0) { return integerPart; // No decimal part, keep as integer } else if (decimalPart >= 0.5) { return Math.round(roundedToTwoDecimals); // Round to the nearest integer } else { return roundedToTwoDecimals; // Otherwise, keep the two-decimal format } }

function(num) { // First round to two decimal places if needed var roundedToTwoDecimals = Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Check if the result after two-decimal rounding has a decimal part of .00 or .50+ var integerPart = Math.floor(roundedToTwoDecimals); var decimalPart = roundedToTwoDecimals - integerPart; if (decimalPart === 0) { return integerPart; // No decimal part, keep as integer } else if (decimalPart >= 0.5) { return Math.round(roundedToTwoDecimals); // Round to the nearest integer } else { return roundedToTwoDecimals; // Otherwise, keep the two-decimal format } }
